<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4538608>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 5. — Stoliczkella crenatula (Stoliczka,1862),n. comb.; A, general view of lectotype; B, autozooecial apertures with suboral avicularia smaller than those in Stoliczkella subovata n. comb. (cf. Fig. 3F); C, partly preserved ooecium; D, older stage of colony development showing secondary calcification; E, autozooecia with deeply immersed ooecia and small avicularia; F, autozooecial aperture with proximal depression accommodating areolar pores. Scale bars: A, D, 1 mm; B, C, E, F, 100 μm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4538608/files/figure.png" .

